incipit: I would find her society much more believable if it was set far in the future on some other planet, and did not require the reader to swallow a total reversal of current trends.

Uncommon Women (1983)

A shallow cash-grab. More troubling is the is the lecturing on the evils of capitalism and how it was responsible for all the ecological troubles of the world. The lecturing is reasonable for the characters and their background, and makes sense given the characters' situation.
